ents are noted in each advertisement  Address cover letters to Search Committee for the recruiting department  Mail to address listed in advertisement along with requested information by the advertised deadline  Classified and Wage positions  A state application is required  In addition to the state application  you may submit a resume or any other materials appropriate for use to evaluate your skills  training  education  etc  A copy of your application materials may be faxed to 540 464 7299 or emailed to hr vmi edu to meet the deadline  However  original materials must follow by mail or in person  State guidelines require our office to have a state application with original signature on file  Applications must be received in our office by 4 30 p m  on the deadline  Postmarks will not be honored  Select positions are now accepting online applications through the Virginia State Job Site  Instructions for creating an account and applying to positions are included in the link  These position postings will include a hyperlink to the site and specify that online applications are accepted  You can also use this site to complete the state application and print for positions not yet accepting online applications  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   How to Apply for Employment  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrati